#17720 üêû Bug report

### Command (mark with an `x`)
- [x] serve

### Is this a regression?
Not sure.  Haven't seen this work correctly yet.

### Description
When using build configurations for ng build you can overwrite the default build options.  For example you set the optimization option to 'true' in the default section and overwrite it to 'false' for a local testing configuration.  Ng build works fine and you get what you would expect.  When you use ng serve and specify that configuration you end up getting a mix of the default values and the configuration values.  Specifically, you seem to get the default values set in the ng build section for options that match naming of options that exist in ng serve.  I.E.  The optimization setting when using ng serve is now 'true' instead of getting 'false'.  If you simply remove the default setting in ng build it now correctly picks up the configuration setting.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
Here is a sample angular.json stripped down to just the necessary bits.
<pre><code>
{
    "projects": {
        "test": {
            "architect": {
                "build": {
                    "options": {
                        "optimization": true
                    },
                    "configurations": {
                        "local": {
                            "optimization": false
                        }
                    }
                },
                "serve": {
                    "options": {
                        "browserTarget": "test:build"
                    },
                    "configurations": {
                        "local": {
                            "browserTarget": "test:build:local"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
</code></pre>

When running `ng serve -c local` you end up with optimization set to true.  If you remove the default value it picks up the value in the configuration.

