**Anything else relevant?**
I believe the inheritance only fails to work on properties that have a similar name for both ng serve and ng build.  For example the optimization option is available for both.

**Current workaround**
To address the issue and still allow me to have a default i'm currently setting those properties in both the build and serve section.
<pre><code>
{
    "projects": {
        "test": {
            "architect": {
                "build": {
                    "options": {
                        "optimization": true
                    },
                    "configurations": {
                        "local": {
                            "optimization": false
                        }
                    }
                },
                "serve": {
                    "options": {
                        "browserTarget": "test:build"
                    },
                    "configurations": {
                        "local": {
                            "browserTarget": "test:build:local",
                            "optimization": false
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
</code></pre>
